National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan spoke with Akiba Takeo, Secretary General of Japan's National Security Secretariat, to discuss the situation in Russia and Ukraine. Sullivan highlighted that Russian forces are still prepared to attack Ukraine. They talked about diplomatic efforts and reiterated President Biden's stance on diplomacy. Sullivan expressed gratitude for Japan's decision to redirect some Liquefied Natural Gas supplies to Europe. They emphasized the importance of a strong international response to Russian aggression, with Japan committed to coordinating with the United States and the G-7.